
	<sn><md>## Land and Sea Breeze

Land and sea breezes are **local winds** that occur due to the **unequal heating and cooling of land and sea**. These winds are most common in **coastal regions** and usually happen on a **daily cycle**.

---

![diagram](https://cdn.britannica.com/69/62669-050-FBD897CC/paths-sea-breeze-land.jpg?w=300)

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
### Daytime ‚òÄÔ∏è{.text-center}
1. **During the day**, land heats up faster than the sea.
2. The **air above the land** becomes warmer, lighter, and rises, creating a **low-pressure zone**.
3. The **air over the sea** remains cooler and denser, creating a **high-pressure zone**.
4. The cool air from the sea flows toward the land to replace the rising warm air ‚Üí this is called the **sea breeze**.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
### Nighttime üåô{.text-center}
1. **At night**, land cools down faster than the sea.
2. The **air above the land** becomes cooler and denser, creating a **high-pressure zone**.
3. The **air over the sea** remains relatively warmer, creating a **low-pressure zone**.
4. The cooler air from the land flows toward the sea to replace the rising warm air ‚Üí this is called the **land breeze**.
:::

:::

+++ Key Differences

| Feature             | Sea Breeze (Day)                      | Land Breeze (Night)                   |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Time of Occurrence  | Daytime                               | Nighttime                             |
| Heating Pattern     | Land heats faster, sea remains cooler | Land cools faster, sea remains warmer |
| Pressure on Land    | Low pressure                          | High pressure                         |
| Pressure on Sea     | High pressure                         | Low pressure                          |
| Wind Direction      | From sea to land                      | From land to sea                      |
| Temperature of Wind | Cool breeze                           | Warm breeze                           |

+++</md></sn>		
